The paper addresses the issue of learning from synthetic domain randomized data effectively, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed algorithm involves adversarial training, which is a popular technique in deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of simulators, which are commonly used in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
